"{\"uid\": \"thestar.com.my-tech-tech-news-2024-08-05-google-pulls-ai-ad-that-irked-some-olympics-viewers\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"Monday, 05 Aug 2024  Tech evangelists have touted the promised benefits of AI, but teachers, musicians, artists and others have accused its creators of training advanced computers to replace them.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 196, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 75, \"end\": 77, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Artificial_intelligence\", \"score\": 0.999998906058552, \"rank\": 1.0924850946859462e-06, \"text\": \"AI\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Artificial_intelligence\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Artificial_intelligence\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"- Reuters  SAN FRANCISCO:Google confirmed on Aug 2 that it had pulled an ad for its Gemini artificial intelligence after it landed flat with some Olympics viewers.\", \"from\": 197, \"to\": 360, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 222, \"end\": 228, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Google\", \"score\": 0.9988144438322598, \"rank\": 0.0011869498656771039, \"text\": \"Google\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Google\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Google\"}, {\"begin\": 281, \"end\": 287, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Project_Gemini\", \"score\": 0.5714489210409271, \"rank\": 0.7499376814573137, \"text\": \"Gemini\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Project_Gemini\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Project_Gemini\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The \\\"Dear Sydney\\\" ad, intended to tout capabilities of Gemini AI, featured a dad warmly describing how the tool wrote his daughter a fan letter from her to US hurdler Sydney McLaughlin-Levrone.\", \"from\": 362, \"to\": 555, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 417, \"end\": 423, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Project_Gemini\", \"score\": 0.5714489210409271, \"rank\": 0.7499376814573137, \"text\": \"Gemini\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Project_Gemini\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Project_Gemini\"}, {\"begin\": 424, \"end\": 426, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Artificial_intelligence\", \"score\": 0.999998906058552, \"rank\": 1.0924850946859462e-06, \"text\": \"AI\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Artificial_intelligence\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Artificial_intelligence\"}, {\"begin\": 518, \"end\": 520, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.9968792268890287, \"rank\": 0.0010512849087525328, \"text\": \"US\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}, {\"begin\": 529, \"end\": 535, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sydney\", \"score\": 0.9999920245060997, \"rank\": 4.128358720910807e-06, \"text\": \"Sydney\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sydney\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sydney\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"However, some viewers bashed the ad as promoting the notion that parents should coax their children to rely on AI rather than learn to express themselves.\", \"from\": 557, \"to\": 711, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 668, \"end\": 670, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Artificial_intelligence\", \"score\": 0.999998906058552, \"rank\": 1.0924850946859462e-06, \"text\": \"AI\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Artificial_intelligence\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Artificial_intelligence\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"While the ad tested well before airing, given the feedback, we have decided to phase the ad out of our Olympics rotation,\\\" a Google spokesperson told AFP.\", \"from\": 713, \"to\": 868, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 864, \"end\": 867, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Agence_France-Presse\", \"score\": 0.9999996766619529, \"rank\": 2.9256866807288175e-07, \"text\": \"AFP\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Agence_France-Presse\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Agence_France-Presse\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Social media posts fired off on an array of platforms questioned whether the ad signaled a dystopian future in which human creativity atrophies due to AI.\", \"from\": 870, \"to\": 1024, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1021, \"end\": 1023, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Artificial_intelligence\", \"score\": 0.999998906058552, \"rank\": 1.0924850946859462e-06, \"text\": \"AI\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Artificial_intelligence\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Artificial_intelligence\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Syracuse University media professor Shelly Palmer said the commercial suggested that a poorly worded prompt to a generative AI tool can express a person's feeling better than they could themselves.\", \"from\": 1026, \"to\": 1223, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1026, \"end\": 1045, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Syracuse_University\", \"score\": 0.9999987173161158, \"rank\": 7.307239918515008e-07, \"text\": \"Syracuse University\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q3918\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q2385804\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Syracuse_University\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Syracuse_University\"}, {\"begin\": 1062, \"end\": 1075, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Shelly_Palmer\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Shelly Palmer\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Shelly_Palmer\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Shelly_Palmer\"}, {\"begin\": 1150, \"end\": 1152, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Artificial_intelligence\", \"score\": 0.999998906058552, \"rank\": 1.0924850946859462e-06, \"text\": \"AI\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Artificial_intelligence\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Artificial_intelligence\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"This commercial showing somebody having a child use AI to write a fan letter to her hero sucks,\\\" author Linda Holmes wrote in a post on BlueSky.\", \"from\": 1225, \"to\": 1370, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1278, \"end\": 1280, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Artificial_intelligence\", \"score\": 0.999998906058552, \"rank\": 1.0924850946859462e-06, \"text\": \"AI\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Artificial_intelligence\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Artificial_intelligence\"}, {\"begin\": 1330, \"end\": 1342, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Linda_Holmes\", \"score\": 0.9999999999533884, \"rank\": 4.660609677134535e-11, \"text\": \"Linda Holmes\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Linda_Holmes\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Linda_Holmes\"}, {\"begin\": 1362, \"end\": 1369, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bluesky,_Alberta\", \"score\": 0.934115051658946, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"BlueSky\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bluesky,_Alberta\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bluesky,_Alberta\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Who wants an AI-written fan letter?\\\"\", \"from\": 1372, \"to\": 1409, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Tech evangelists have touted the promised benefits of AI, but teachers, musicians, artists and others have accused its creators of training advanced computers to replace them.\", \"from\": 1411, \"to\": 1586, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1465, \"end\": 1467, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Artificial_intelligence\", \"score\": 0.999998906058552, \"rank\": 1.0924850946859462e-06, \"text\": \"AI\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Artificial_intelligence\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Artificial_intelligence\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Early this year, Apple had an ad stumble of its own with a commercial showing musical instruments, paint cans and other creative gear crushed and replaced by an iPad to the tune of a song titledAll I Ever Need Is You.\", \"from\": 1588, \"to\": 1805, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1605, \"end\": 1610, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Apple_Inc.\", \"score\": 0.9999999999815827, \"rank\": 1.8408760095282743e-11, \"text\": \"Apple\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Apple_Inc.\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Apple_Inc.\"}, {\"begin\": 1749, \"end\": 1753, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/IPad\", \"score\": 0.9967282005265122, \"rank\": 0.0032822767801371122, \"text\": \"iPad\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/IPad\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/IPad\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"- AFP  Thank you for your report!\", \"from\": 1806, \"to\": 1839, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Copyright \\u00a9 1995-Star Media Group Berhad [197101000523 (10894-D)]  Best viewed on Chrome browsers.\", \"from\": 1841, \"to\": 1939, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1923, \"end\": 1929, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Google_Chrome\", \"score\": 0.9982167336180258, \"rank\": 0.001786452066719927, \"text\": \"Chrome\", \"types\": [\"Q7397\", \"Q386724\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Google_Chrome\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Google_Chrome\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"We would love to keep you posted on the latest promotion.\", \"from\": 1943, \"to\": 2000, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Kindly fill the form below  We hope you enjoy this feature!\", \"from\": 2001, \"to\": 2060, \"entities\": []}]}"